<paragraph blockId="155.[151,1437,1036,1990]" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis box="[151,235,1037,1062]" italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Leaves</emphasis>
veins raised and rectangular in cross-section adaxially; basal pinna 3.0(0.5–14.0) cm wide; apical pinna 10.6(2.0–30.0) cm wide. 
<emphasis box="[524,693,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Inflorescences</emphasis>
prophyll margins with irregular, spine-like projections; flower pits usually spirally arranged, not distantly spaced.
</paragraph>
